column2: At that stage  the  Appellant has  invoked  revisionary  jurisdiction of
the Provincial High Court seeking to challenge the validity of the issuance

column1: revision, the Provincial High Court has held that there was no illegality in

column2: the  issuance  of  writ of possession  by  the  Magistrate's  Court.  It also  held
that the Respondent is  the Competent Authority who could move for  the
issuance of writ of possession against the Appellant.
